                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90G/9–1245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moreland</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-19T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 19, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>284. Your 353 Sep 12. You may inform your Brit colleague that while the question
                    of raising the rank of our representatives in certain Near Eastern countries has
                    recd our attention from time to time and may come up again for consideration in
                    the not distant future we have no intention of proceeding without prior
                    discussion with the Brit Govt.</p>
                <p>Sent Baghdad. Repeated Cairo and London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
